---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Wyandot Snacks — Customer Story — Formic"
  description="Founded in 1936 and once maker of a quarter of the world's popcorn, Wyandot Snacks used Formic's Full Service model to take the strain off palletizing and scale for a major new customer."
  ogTitle="Wyandot Snacks — Formic Customer Story"
  ogDescription="90 years of snacks · built for agility · no jobs cut"
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/stories/wyandot-snacks" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/stories">Customer Stories</a><span class="sep">/</span>Wyandot Snacks
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Customer Story · Wyandot Snacks</div>
    <h1 style="font-size:clamp(32px,3.8vw,56px)">90 Years of Snacks, Now Built for Agility: Wyandot Snacks Automates to Scale Production</h1>
    <p class="lede">Founded in 1936 and once the maker of more than a quarter of the world's popcorn, Wyandot Snacks turned to Formic's Full Service model to take the strain off palletizing — and say "yes" to a major new customer without compromising 90 years of values.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <img src="/stories/wyandot-snacks-hero.jpg" alt="Wyandot Snacks production and palletizing" />
      <span class="dv-cap">Wyandot Snacks · Marion, Ohio</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:64px 0 0">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 80px">
    <div class="db-tag">At a glance</div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(150px,1fr));gap:1px;background:var(--lgrey);border:1px solid var(--lgrey);margin-top:14px">
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Founded</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">1936</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Location</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Marion, Ohio</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Industry</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">Snack co-manufacturing</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">In business</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">90 years</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--white);padding:18px 20px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mgrey);margin-bottom:6px">Claim to fame</div><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:17px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.01em;color:var(--black)">25% of world's popcorn</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — The Challenge</div>
      <h2>Say "yes" more often, <em>without breaking the line</em>.</h2>
      <p>From a Depression-era popcorn company to a full-service snack co-manufacturer — extruded snacks, baked snacks, cereals, chips, and popcorn — Wyandot lives with frequent SKU changes, varying run sizes, and tight timelines. A major new customer required many millions of additional pounds of product, and existing labor gaps were straining capacity.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Frequent SKU changes and varying run sizes</li>
        <li>New customer requiring millions more pounds</li>
        <li>Labor gaps straining production capacity</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/stories/wyandot-snacks-2.jpg" alt="Wyandot Snacks palletizing line" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Popcorn · snacks · cereals</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Wyandot-Palletizing.jpg" alt="Wyandot palletizing automation" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Full Service · swappable</span></div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — The Solution</div>
      <h2>Full Service, <em>after a hard lesson</em>.</h2>
      <p>Five years earlier, Wyandot bought case packers — building comfort with automation while clarifying its need for flexibility. For palletizing it chose Formic's Full Service model over buying: no upfront capital, quick implementation, ongoing support, and equipment swapping, plus real-time data on energy use, bottlenecks, and scheduling. Workers move to operation, maintenance, and supervisory roles, supported by a new automation certification program.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>No upfront capital, quick implementation</li>
        <li>Equipment swapping and ongoing support</li>
        <li>Automation certification program for the team</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white" style="padding:88px 80px">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0">
    <div class="pull-quote">
      <blockquote>"The snack industry is moving faster and becoming more specialized. Our investment in automation is about meeting those demands without compromising the values this company has upheld for nearly 90 years: quality, safety, community, and employee wellbeing."</blockquote>
      <cite>Jaap Langenberg · CEO, Wyandot Snacks</cite>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="si" style="max-width:1280px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px;text-align:center">
    <div class="db-tag" style="justify-content:center">03 — The Outcome</div>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:clamp(40px,5vw,72px);font-weight:500;letter-spacing:-.02em;line-height:1;color:var(--white);margin:18px 0 56px">Built on the legacy, <em style="color:var(--orange);font-style:normal">not despite it.</em></h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.1)">
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">90</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Years of snacks</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">25%</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Of world's popcorn</div></div>
      <div style="background:var(--black);padding:36px 24px"><div style="font-family:var(--sans);font-size:48px;font-weight:500;color:var(--orange);line-height:1">0</div><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(240,245,241,.55);margin-top:12px">Jobs eliminated</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Build your next <em>90 years</em>.</h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/stories" class="btn-ctawh">More Customer Stories</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
